# Hoboken Helo Accountability Tracker — environment variable reference
#
# Stages 1–4 require NO secrets beyond the automatic GITHUB_TOKEN.
# Everything below is Stage 5 only. Do not configure these until
# Stages 1–4 have run cleanly for at least two weeks.
#
# Store all Stage 5 values in GitHub Secrets, NOT in this file.
# This file is checked into the repo and must never contain real values.
# The actual .env file is in .gitignore and must never be committed.

# ── Stage 5 only ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Resend API key — create a sending-scope-only key; do not use a full-access key.
# RESEND_API_KEY=

# Sending address — must be verified in your Resend account/domain.
# MAIL_FROM=

# Reply-To address — routes responses to your Proton Mail inbox.
# MAIL_REPLY_TO=

# Filer identity — appears verbatim in every complaint letter.
# For local dev/testing, use placeholder values:
#   FILER_NAME=Test User
#   FILER_ADDRESS=123 Test Street, Test City NJ 00000
# Never use real PII in test data or commits.
# FILER_NAME=
# FILER_ADDRESS=
# FILER_EMAIL=
# FILER_PHONE=
